h the panel just opened on it ‚Äî the reviewer sees story B's baseline image by default instead of the diff they'd expect when first reviewing a changed/new result, and only self-corrects to a different tab if story B happens to lack a baseline artifact (via the `availableImages.at(-1)` fallback).\",\"category\":\"correctness\",\"verdict\":\"CONFIRMED\"},{\"file\":\"packages/storybook-addon-visual-tests/src/node/runner.ts\",\"line\":199,\"summary\":\"approve() flips a result's status to 'passed' without clearing or regenerating its stale diff/candidate artifact references from the pre-approval comparison.\",\"failure_scenario\":\"Reviewer approves a 'changed' result (baseline overwritten with the just-captured candidate on disk via approveCandidate). The in-memory `publicResult` still carries `artifacts.diff` pointing at the old diff.png (baseline-vs-candidate delta) and the pre-approval `message`/`diffPixels` are left stale on the object (only `status` and `message` for the 'passed' label are overwritten, `diffPixels`/`diffRatio`/`artifacts` are not cleared) ‚Äî if the reviewer reopens the 'Diff' tab for that story in the same session they see a nonzero visual diff image next to a 'passed' status badge, which reads as contradictory/misleading even though no data corruption occurs.\",\"category\":\"correctness\",\"verdict\":\"CONFIRMED\"},{\"file\":\"packages/storybook-addon-visual-tests/src/node/runner.ts\",\"line\":96,\"summary\":\"VisualTestRunner.run() unconditionally clears the entire `completed` map and replaces the whole `state.results` array with only the newly-selected story/stories, even for a 'current' (single-story) run ‚Äî but TestProviderRow.tsx aggregates counts over the full `state.results` and Panel/approve() rely on `completed` entries surviving across runs of other stories. [same root cause also at: packages/storybook-addon-visual-tests/src/node/runner.ts:92]\",\"failure_scenario\":\"User runs 'Run all' (TestProviderRow), which flags e.g. two stories as new/changed (visible as '2 changed' in the test-provider row and reviewable via Accept in the Panel). User then opens a third, unrelated story and clicks 'Run visual tests' for just that story (PanelView's `runCurrent` -&gt; `{type:'run', scope:'current', storyId}`). `VisualTestRunner.run()` synchronously calls `this.completed.clear()` and then sets `this.state = run.state` where `run.state.results` contains only the one just-selected story. The two previously-flagged stories vanish from `state.results`, so TestProviderRow now shows '0 changed'/'No visual changes detected' even though those two diffs were never reviewed or approved, and if the user later returns to one of those stories and clicks Accept, `approve()` finds no matching entry in `completed` and throws 'Stale visual approval; rerun the visual test before approving' ‚Äî silently losing reviewable work with no warning that it happened.\",\"category\":\"correctness\",\"verdict\":\"CONFIRMED\"},{\"file\":\"packages/storybook-addon-visual-tests/src/node/runner.ts\",\"line\":400,\"summary\":\"isMissing() duplicates isMissingPathError() in paths.ts verbatim instead of importing it\",\"failure_scenario\":\"The identical ENOENT/ENOTDIR-check function body exists in two files (runner.ts:400-406 and paths.ts:139-145); a future change to what counts as a 'missing file' error (e.g. adding EISDIR handling) has to be made in both places, and it's easy to update one and forget the other, silently reintroducing the bug the fix was meant to close in only one of the two call sites.\",\"category\":\"cleanup\",\"verdict\":\"CONFIRMED\"},{\"file\":\"packages/storybook-addon-visual-tests/src/node/runner.ts\",\"line\":307,\"summary\":\"finishCapture reads baseline.png and baseline.json sequentially instead of in parallel\",\"failure_scenario\":\"readFileIfPresent(paths.baselinePath) and readJsonIfPresent(paths.baselineMetadataPath) are two independent, unrelated file reads awaited one after another for every story in every run; running them via Promise.all would halve this per-story I/O latency with no change in behavior, and the cost compounds across a full-suite run (runPool already parallelizes across stories, so this serialization tax is paid once per story capture).\",\"category\":\"cleanup\",\"verdict\":\"CONFIRMED\"},{\"file\":\"packages/storybook-addon-visual-tests/src/node/capture.ts\",\"line\":271,\"summary\":\"contentClip() computes getBoundingClientRect() twice per visible element\",\"failure_scenario\":\"The filter callback (line 261) already computes each element's getBoundingClientRect() to test visibility, discards it, and the subsequent .map() (line 271) recomputes getBoundingClientRect() for the same elements again. On a story with a large DOM (e.g. a data table or the addon's own Panel), this doubles the per-element layout-read cost of a full document.body.querySelectorAll('*') scan that already runs on every single captured story; carrying the already-computed rectangle forward (e.g. filter+map into {element, rectangle} tuples once) does the same job for half the layout reads.\",\"category\":\"cleanup\",\"verdict\":\"CONFIRMED\"},{\"file\":\"packages/storybook-addon-visual-tests/src/manager/Panel.stories.tsx\",\"line\":58,\"summary\":\"None of the 5 new stories carry the required 'ai-generated' provenance tag\",\"failure_scenario\":\".claude/rules/stories.md states \\\"Every story an agent writes MUST be tagged 'ai-generated' (in that story's own tags)... An agent must never create a story without it.\\\" ReviewChanges, NoResult, CaptureError, Running, and StaticUnavailable in this file have no `tags` field at all. Because apps/storybook/.storybook/main.ts now globs `packages/storybook-addon-visual-tests/src/**/*.stories.@(ts|tsx)` into the Storybook stories config, these stories feed the addon-mcp manifest without the provenance marker human reviewers rely on to know the story was AI-authored.\",\"category\":\"cleanup\",\"verdict\":\"CONFIRMED\"},{\"file\":\"p